<li id="cite_note-Moravia_p._69-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Moravia_p._69_6-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Moravia_p._69_6-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">"Clamores Eliae" he dedicated "To my lovely mother, Moravia, one of her faithful son...". Clamores Eliae, p. 69, Kastellaun/Hunsrück&#160;: A. Henn, 1977.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-uni-mannheim.de-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-uni-mannheim.de_7-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-uni-mannheim.de_7-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">"Moravian by nation, language Bohemian, profession theologian, servant of Gospel from the year of grace 1616." It is his own identification in "Opera omnia didactica" 1657, <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.uni-mannheim.de/mateo/camenaref/comenius/comenius1/p3/jpg/s468.html">http://www.uni-mannheim.de/mateo/camenaref/comenius/comenius1/p3/jpg/s468.html</a></span>
</li>
